description:
&lt;p&gt;Poppy Unit is a twenty bed inpatient unit in the heart of Wiltshire, nestled between the historic monuments of Avebury and Stonehenge to the south, and the Vale of Pewsey and the Marlborough Downs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Located on the Green Lane Hospital site, the successful candidate would be working alongside the Place of Safety, ECT and Early Intervention Services, as well as the Community Mental Health teams and on-site AMPH service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The local town of Devizes is a vibrant and buzzing market town with a café culture and serviced by an array of artisans, festivals and tourism.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be a qualified mental health nurse, looking either to complete their preceptorship or to develop their career through development of the service. Poppy Unit currently operates through the safe wards initiative and is piloting the CQC lead sexual safety collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Poppy offer a successful preceptorship with experienced nurses to help commence your journey into nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:   Robyn Laney, Senior Practitioner 01380 731207.&lt;/p&gt;
